<Title>Main Landing Gear (Body) Door Seals</Title>
<DispatchCondition>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>Eight per door may be missing ( 787-9) and nine per door may be missing (787-10), for a total length of 21.25 feet, provided landing gear remains extended for 10 minutes after takeoff and the takeoff performance adjustment is applied.  Seals along the inboard edge of the door (2 seals per door) and the forward edge of
the door inboard of the door vent ( 2 seals per door for 787-9 or 787-10) may not be missing.</Para>
<Para>Procedure:
Do not retract landing gear for 10 minutes after takeoff. In the event of an engine failure after V1, retract the landing gear until a minimum of 1,500 feet above airport elevation and terrain clearance is assured. While maintaining terrain clearance, extend the gear for the balance of the 10 minutes.</Para>
