<Note>
<Para>The CDL penalty for seals missing is negligible and the above procedure does not apply when operating with the landing gear extended (Appendix 1) for the entire flight.</Para>
</Note>
<Para>**NOTE: For the 787-9, the minimum takeoff penalty for this item is 2,000 lb. The higher of either the minimum penalty or the calculated penalty for seal missing must be used. The penalty for a missing seal is 150 lb/foot. When more than 13 feet, 4 inches of seal is missing, the penalty must be calculated based on the amount of seal missing.**</Para>
<Para>For 787-9, increase flight planning fuel by 2,900 pounds (1,315 kg) for landing gear extended for 10 minutes.</Para>
<Para>For 787-10, increase flight planning fuel by 2,800 pounds (1,270 kg) for landing gear extended for 10 minutes.</Para>
